CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 5, 1958 , pg. 1 reads: "After Three of Seven Wrecks - These automobiles were among those damaged in seven crashes last week and this week. The wrecks in which these cars were involved occurred in East Liberty, Homewood and the Hill District...A stolen car, right, smashed into a plate glass window of John Mosby's barber shop in the hill, and its four youthful passengers escaped before police arrived. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Light colored car with front end damage, parked in lot with other automobiles including Plymouth on left side, truck inscribed "Hammel's Express" and factory in background
